The paper deals with approximate linear programming techniques for Markov Decision Processes, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses optimization techniques (cs.RO) and decomposition of problems (cs.DS), which are relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with probabilistic planning (cs.PL), which is a specific application of AI and machine learning.
